article.description: Anderson leads North Dakota past Montana St. 72-69
article.headline: Anderson leads North Dakota past Montana St. 72-69
article.linkText: Anderson leads North Dakota past Montana St. 72-69
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- Aaron Anderson scored 18 points, Troy Huff added 13 as North Dakota held on to defeat Montana State 72-69 Saturday night. Flavien Davis scored a layup and was fouled to pull Montana State within 70-69 with 48 seconds to play, but he missed the ensuing free throw. Anderson then answered with two free throws to cap the scoring. Stephan Holm missed a potential game-tying 3-pointer with 3 seconds left for Montana State. Anderson hit a 3-pointer to give North Dakota its largest lead, 54-43 with 16:37 remaining. He finished 5 of 10 from the field, including four 3-pointers. North Dakota(6-10, 3-3 Big Sky) won its first road game of the season. Davis scored 10 of his 25 points in the final five minutes to lead Montana State (9-8, 4-2 Big Sky). Paul Eqwuonwu added 14 points for the Bobcats.
